<section class="about-main">
    <div class="about-container">

        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
            The American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) student section at BITS Pilani
            isn’t just a club; we are a multidisciplinary R&D team. We bridge the gap between
            mechanical design, control systems, software integration, and data analytics to
            build systems that scale.
        </p>

        <p>
            Instead of limiting ourselves to short-term participation in college events, we focus
            on long-term, 3–4 semester projects aimed at commercial viability and intellectual
            property generation.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Approach & Tech Stack</h2>
        <p>
            We don’t just assemble off-the-shelf parts. Our workflow spans the entire engineering
            pipeline — from rapid prototyping and custom CAD design (Fusion 360, SolidWorks)
            to advanced simulations (Ansys, CFD) and autonomous systems (ROS2, MATLAB/Simulink).
        </p>

        <p>
            Whether transitioning micromouse prototypes from perf boards to custom PCBs or
            machining high-torque drum spinners for combat robots, we emphasize industrial-grade
            fabrication, iterative design, and rigorous testing.
        </p>

        <h2>What Sets Us Apart</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Multidisciplinary integration across mechanical, electronics, and software systems</li>
            <li>Focus on real-world industrial applications, not just academic prototypes</li>
            <li>Long-term project cycles aimed at scalability and commercialization</li>
            <li>Strong emphasis on intellectual property and innovation</li>
        </ul>

    </div>
</section>
